1
00:00:10,567 --> 00:00:12,367
<i> Your fight begins now.</i>

2
00:00:12,500 --> 00:00:14,533
<i> You're on the offensive side.</i>

3
00:00:14,667 --> 00:00:17,167
<i>Don't let them get ahead of you.</i>

4
00:00:17,300 --> 00:00:18,833
<i>Why are you looking
at that woman?</i>

5
00:00:18,967 --> 00:00:20,867
<i> She seems familiar to me.</i>

6
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:23,633
<i> Mookie is so evil, right?</i>

7
00:00:23,767 --> 00:00:25,067
<i> Weird.</i>

8
00:00:25,200 --> 00:00:26,833
<i> Oh my God!</i>

9
00:00:26,967 --> 00:00:28,933
<i> I need to get to Danilo first.</i>

10
00:00:29,067 --> 00:00:30,133
<i> Jade really doesn't stop.</i>

11
00:00:30,267 --> 00:00:31,400
<i>She's looking in your direction.</i>

12
00:00:31,533 --> 00:00:33,900
<i>I'm Jade Caparas
of Artemis Pharmacy.</i>

13
00:00:34,067 --> 00:00:35,700
<i>- And you are?
- May I call on Jade Caparas.</i>

14
00:00:35,833 --> 00:00:38,167
<i>You're good at this. Right?
Bring her to me.</i>

15
00:00:38,300 --> 00:00:39,067
<i> Zayn?</i>

16
00:00:42,433 --> 00:00:43,200
<i> Help!</i>

17
00:00:43,333 --> 00:00:45,067
<i> Emma?</i>

18
00:00:45,200 --> 00:00:47,100
<i>Love, I'll use the restroom
quickly.</i>

19
00:00:47,233 --> 00:00:48,133
<i> You like me, don't you?</i>

20
00:00:48,267 --> 00:00:50,633
<i>I thought you were my wife,
Emma.</i>

21
00:00:50,767 --> 00:00:55,200
<i>He still treats me as his wife
after replacing me with Jade.</i>

22
00:01:40,033 --> 00:01:41,800
Mookie!

23
00:01:41,967 --> 00:01:43,267
Mookie, I'm sorry.

24
00:01:44,600 --> 00:01:46,267
Help.

25
00:01:46,400 --> 00:01:48,133
Let's talk, please.

26
00:01:52,033 --> 00:01:56,133
- Zayn! Help!
- Mookie!

27
00:01:58,333 --> 00:02:00,133
What are you going to do to me?

28
00:02:00,267 --> 00:02:02,433
- Zayn!
- Mookie!

29
00:02:03,533 --> 00:02:05,200
- Zayn!
- Mooks!

30
00:02:11,533 --> 00:02:13,033
Stop it!

31
00:02:13,167 --> 00:02:16,267
What do you want from us?
Leave Zayn alone!

32
00:02:16,433 --> 00:02:25,867
Hey! Stop it! Leave Zayn alone!

33
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:27,867
Stop it! Hey!

34
00:02:35,233 --> 00:02:36,233
Who are you?

35
00:02:39,300 --> 00:02:40,767
Zayn! Help!

36
00:02:40,900 --> 00:02:44,067
Mookie! Hey! Who are you?
I'll call the police!

37
00:02:44,200 --> 00:02:45,833
Hey! What are you doing
to Mookie?

38
00:02:45,967 --> 00:02:46,967
Who are they?

39
00:02:48,700 --> 00:02:50,567
What happened?

40
00:02:50,700 --> 00:02:51,833
Zayn!

41
00:02:51,967 --> 00:02:52,933
Are you okay?

42
00:02:54,200 --> 00:02:56,933
- Loida, let's bring him inside.
- Okay, let's go.

43
00:02:57,067 --> 00:02:59,267
Let's get inside.

44
00:02:59,400 --> 00:03:01,500
What if we bring you
to the hospital?

45
00:03:04,400 --> 00:03:05,200
Slowly.

46
00:03:05,333 --> 00:03:07,467
We must report this
to the police.

47
00:03:07,600 --> 00:03:11,133
Look at what they did to you.
Who are they, Mookie?

48
00:03:13,367 --> 00:03:15,633
Is she the woman you were
with earlier?

49
00:03:15,767 --> 00:03:17,200
Is she your wife?

50
00:03:19,267 --> 00:03:20,467
No.

51
00:03:20,600 --> 00:03:22,233
That's Jade.

52
00:03:22,400 --> 00:03:23,867
That's her sister.

53
00:03:26,067 --> 00:03:27,467
Emma's gone.

54
00:03:30,533 --> 00:03:31,767
She left me.

55
00:03:32,867 --> 00:03:33,700
Why?

56
00:03:35,100 --> 00:03:38,433
Is it because you replaced her
with another woman?

57
00:03:38,567 --> 00:03:39,233
What?

58
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:42,900
Sorry.

59
00:03:43,033 --> 00:03:45,167
My questions seem to be getting
too personal.

60
00:03:46,800 --> 00:03:48,033
No, no.

61
00:03:48,167 --> 00:03:49,667
It's okay.

62
00:03:49,800 --> 00:03:53,567
Sorry to bother you.
I'll go back to my place.

63
00:03:54,667 --> 00:03:55,967
No judgment.

64
00:03:57,467 --> 00:04:02,000
As they say, strangers make
the best listener.

65
00:04:02,133 --> 00:04:06,167
So you can tell me anything
about your life.

66
00:04:09,333 --> 00:04:12,167
So, are you and Jade together?

67
00:04:15,300 --> 00:04:16,167
Yes.

68
00:04:17,967 --> 00:04:20,900
Too bad you and Emma are over.

69
00:04:21,033 --> 00:04:25,433
But it's a good thing her
sister is there.

70
00:04:25,567 --> 00:04:27,667
You love someone else now.

71
00:04:27,833 --> 00:04:32,700
But for me, the original
is still the best.

72
00:04:32,833 --> 00:04:33,800
The real one.

73
00:04:33,933 --> 00:04:35,267
The one you're accustomed to.

74
00:04:36,667 --> 00:04:41,500
Just like my perfume,
I wear it all my life.

75
00:04:41,633 --> 00:04:44,267
So, it should never be replaced.

76
00:04:44,400 --> 00:04:45,667
But you know what?

77
00:04:47,467 --> 00:04:51,400
When the person we love leaves
us and chooses someone else,

78
00:04:51,533 --> 00:04:54,467
we also must learn
how to forget them.

79
00:05:19,533 --> 00:05:21,100
It took you forever.

80
00:05:21,233 --> 00:05:22,400
Are you okay now?

81
00:05:22,533 --> 00:05:24,467
Well, I guess.

82
00:05:24,600 --> 00:05:26,333
I don't know.

83
00:05:26,467 --> 00:05:30,200
Why did this have to happen
today of all days?

84
00:05:30,333 --> 00:05:31,033
I know.

85
00:05:31,167 --> 00:05:33,167
We missed the activities
outside.

86
00:05:33,300 --> 00:05:34,667
I know.

87
00:05:34,833 --> 00:05:38,733
And that mysterious lady
with a red face art.

88
00:05:38,867 --> 00:05:40,667
You know what?

89
00:05:40,800 --> 00:05:45,800
I feel something strange about
that woman.

90
00:05:45,933 --> 00:05:47,400
She has...

91
00:05:47,533 --> 00:05:49,400
Emma vibes.

92
00:05:49,533 --> 00:05:51,567
Olive.

93
00:05:51,700 --> 00:05:52,833
Emma's dead.

94
00:05:52,967 --> 00:05:53,833
I know.

95
00:05:53,967 --> 00:05:57,367
That's why I said it's weird.

96
00:05:57,500 --> 00:05:59,600
And you know what?

97
00:05:59,733 --> 00:06:02,333
Danilo seems to see Emma in her
too.

98
00:06:02,467 --> 00:06:04,667
That's why he keeps looking
at her.

99
00:06:04,800 --> 00:06:06,867
Why do you seem jealous?

100
00:06:07,000 --> 00:06:08,100
Why?

101
00:06:08,267 --> 00:06:10,167
Don't I have the right?

102
00:06:10,300 --> 00:06:12,733
He's my fiancé.

103
00:06:12,867 --> 00:06:17,000
And I worked hard
just to get him.

104
00:06:17,133 --> 00:06:18,400
I know.

105
00:06:20,667 --> 00:06:25,467
I'm so tired of being left
behind by the people I love.

106
00:06:27,667 --> 00:06:28,933
So now,

107
00:06:31,133 --> 00:06:36,333
I believe I have the right to be
happy with the person I love.

108
00:06:36,467 --> 00:06:37,700
And that's Danilo.

109
00:06:39,800 --> 00:06:45,000
That's why I won't let anyone
suddenly come in

110
00:06:45,167 --> 00:06:47,200
and just take him away.

111
00:06:49,800 --> 00:06:52,233
I'll get a cold compress
and medicines.

112
00:06:52,367 --> 00:06:53,733
Yes, Loida. Thank you.

113
00:06:58,500 --> 00:06:59,733
Thank you, Mooks.

114
00:07:04,433 --> 00:07:05,967
Are you okay?

115
00:07:06,100 --> 00:07:09,233
We should bring you
to the hospital.

116
00:07:09,367 --> 00:07:11,433
- Loida!
- Mooks, Mooks.

117
00:07:11,567 --> 00:07:12,600
I'm okay.

118
00:07:14,100 --> 00:07:16,333
Zayn, but you're in pain.

119
00:07:16,467 --> 00:07:17,900
I can handle this.

120
00:07:18,033 --> 00:07:20,667
I just got hit over here.

121
00:07:20,800 --> 00:07:24,233
But just a little rest
and I'll be okay.

122
00:07:24,367 --> 00:07:29,567
Your attackers are
the same age as us.

123
00:07:29,700 --> 00:07:31,533
Are there people you
don't get along here?

124
00:07:33,400 --> 00:07:35,233
No one.

125
00:07:35,367 --> 00:07:38,300
But one of the guys seems
familiar to me.

126
00:07:38,433 --> 00:07:40,167
He seems to be Tyler.

127
00:07:40,300 --> 00:07:41,333
Tyler?

128
00:07:41,467 --> 00:07:44,133
Stacy's ex?

129
00:07:44,267 --> 00:07:48,033
Don't tell me that you suspect
Stacy told him to do that.

130
00:07:48,200 --> 00:07:52,033
Duh! Who else wants to hurt me?

131
00:07:52,167 --> 00:07:54,667
Who else wants to get even
with me?

132
00:07:54,800 --> 00:07:57,067
Mooks, stop accusing.

133
00:07:57,200 --> 00:07:59,300
You have no proof.

134
00:07:59,433 --> 00:08:02,800
Zayn, didn't you see the shoes
of the other guy earlier?

135
00:08:02,933 --> 00:08:04,500
That's Tyler's.

136
00:08:04,633 --> 00:08:06,100
Tyler has the same shoes.

137
00:08:06,233 --> 00:08:08,100
I saw it too.

138
00:08:08,233 --> 00:08:10,533
But anyone could own
that kind of shoes.

139
00:08:10,667 --> 00:08:12,233
I have the same shoes too.

140
00:08:12,367 --> 00:08:14,967
You don't believe me anymore.

141
00:08:15,100 --> 00:08:17,533
If you don't want to believe,
then don't.

142
00:08:17,667 --> 00:08:20,800
You ended our friendship anyway.

143
00:08:20,967 --> 00:08:22,200
Mookie, wait.

144
00:08:22,333 --> 00:08:22,967
Wait.

145
00:08:23,100 --> 00:08:24,567
Why are you fighting with me?

146
00:08:24,700 --> 00:08:26,200
What are you doing?

147
00:08:26,333 --> 00:08:28,133
Why did you get up?

148
00:08:29,533 --> 00:08:30,533
Come here.

149
00:08:52,267 --> 00:08:53,367
It's your fault.

150
00:08:54,867 --> 00:08:56,533
You keep getting up.

151
00:09:02,933 --> 00:09:04,333
Here you go, Mookie.

152
00:09:05,467 --> 00:09:10,700
You can go now, Loida.
I'll take it from here.

153
00:09:10,833 --> 00:09:12,333
Are you sure?

154
00:09:12,467 --> 00:09:13,867
Yes.

155
00:09:14,000 --> 00:09:16,767
Okay. I'll go now. Be careful.

156
00:09:16,900 --> 00:09:17,833
Thank you.

157
00:09:17,967 --> 00:09:18,833
Thank you.

158
00:09:29,667 --> 00:09:30,267
Here.

159
00:09:32,533 --> 00:09:33,967
Take it.

160
00:09:43,467 --> 00:09:44,400
Thank you.

161
00:09:59,267 --> 00:10:01,633
Mooks, can you help me?

162
00:10:19,433 --> 00:10:20,400
Do it yourself.

163
00:10:31,233 --> 00:10:32,433
Have some drink.

164
00:10:35,700 --> 00:10:37,600
Thank you.

165
00:10:37,733 --> 00:10:42,100
So, did Emma leave you
for someone else?

166
00:10:42,233 --> 00:10:44,533
She left.

167
00:10:44,667 --> 00:10:45,967
She never showed up again.

168
00:10:47,533 --> 00:10:49,633
She left me for another man.

169
00:10:51,267 --> 00:10:52,933
<i> Really, Danilo?</i>

170
00:10:53,067 --> 00:10:55,933
<i>You brought me to a mental
facility.</i>

171
00:10:56,067 --> 00:10:59,333
<i>And now you're telling me
I went with another man?</i>

172
00:10:59,467 --> 00:11:04,200
<i>Or is that what Jade
made you believe?</i>

173
00:11:09,467 --> 00:11:13,733
How sure are you that she left
you for another man?

174
00:11:15,033 --> 00:11:20,600
Maybe that's just what you want
to believe to justify your sins.

175
00:11:23,367 --> 00:11:25,833
The wrong things you
and Jade did!

176
00:11:25,967 --> 00:11:26,867
Emma?

177
00:11:32,800 --> 00:11:34,267
<i> What the hell, Emma?</i>

178
00:11:34,400 --> 00:11:35,767
<i>You're forgetting about
the plan.</i>

179
00:11:43,433 --> 00:11:45,267
Why are you calling me Emma?

180
00:11:46,800 --> 00:11:50,900
Because you sound like Emma.

181
00:11:52,333 --> 00:11:53,600
I heard her in you.

182
00:11:55,000 --> 00:11:56,333
Is she also an Ilongga?

183
00:11:58,600 --> 00:11:59,733
No.

184
00:12:01,167 --> 00:12:03,300
Earlier, I just smelled like
her.

185
00:12:03,433 --> 00:12:05,967
Now you're saying I sound
like her too.

186
00:12:06,100 --> 00:12:07,533
You know what?

187
00:12:07,667 --> 00:12:11,400
I think you really miss your
wife.

188
00:12:13,300 --> 00:12:14,833
Fine.

189
00:12:15,000 --> 00:12:18,633
I can be Emma,
even just for tonight.

190
00:12:23,733 --> 00:12:27,800
Sorry, but you don't have
to pretend.

191
00:12:27,933 --> 00:12:29,933
Emma isn't like that.

192
00:12:30,067 --> 00:12:31,133
Never mind.

193
00:12:38,067 --> 00:12:40,800
Mooks, can we stop fighting?

194
00:12:40,933 --> 00:12:42,767
Okay, fine.

195
00:12:42,900 --> 00:12:47,100
Starting tomorrow, we will avoid
each other at school.

196
00:12:47,233 --> 00:12:49,367
So we won't fight anymore.

197
00:12:49,533 --> 00:12:52,100
Mooks, can we talk this out,
please?

198
00:12:52,233 --> 00:12:54,700
It's so hard to talk
to you these days.

199
00:12:54,833 --> 00:12:56,933
I know you're going through
something.

200
00:12:57,067 --> 00:12:58,867
But you're way out of line.

201
00:12:59,000 --> 00:13:01,733
You're like Stacy now.
You're so bad.

202
00:13:01,867 --> 00:13:03,433
What's the problem, Mooks?

203
00:13:03,567 --> 00:13:05,067
Tell me.

204
00:13:05,200 --> 00:13:06,700
What's wrong, Mookie?

205
00:13:06,833 --> 00:13:08,000
What is it about?

206
00:13:08,500 --> 00:13:10,367
You know what my problem is?

207
00:13:11,867 --> 00:13:13,400
My mother!

208
00:13:15,933 --> 00:13:19,933
I still can't accept
that she left us.

209
00:13:22,933 --> 00:13:25,100
I hate her so much, Zayn.

210
00:13:27,733 --> 00:13:33,633
I want to not care about
her anymore...

211
00:13:33,767 --> 00:13:35,433
I want to forget her...

212
00:13:35,567 --> 00:13:36,533
But I can't.

213
00:13:38,067 --> 00:13:43,667
I felt how to be a daughter
with her.

214
00:13:46,367 --> 00:13:51,733
When Mommy Olive had been
torturing me,

215
00:13:53,867 --> 00:13:55,700
she was there for me.

216
00:13:58,067 --> 00:14:01,600
She didn't leave me, Zayn.

217
00:14:01,733 --> 00:14:03,533
She helped me.

218
00:14:06,267 --> 00:14:08,400
She protected me.

219
00:14:10,600 --> 00:14:12,867
She cared for me.

220
00:14:17,300 --> 00:14:23,800
And then suddenly, she left me.

221
00:14:25,800 --> 00:14:28,700
Zayn, my mother left me.

222
00:14:47,900 --> 00:14:50,500
Let's just dance.

223
00:14:50,633 --> 00:14:51,267
Wait.

224
00:14:54,600 --> 00:14:55,500
What are you doing?

225
00:15:03,000 --> 00:15:05,333
I don't know how to dance.

226
00:15:05,467 --> 00:15:09,300
I don't believe you. Tell me the
truth.

227
00:15:10,333 --> 00:15:13,400
I only dance with my partner.

228
00:15:13,533 --> 00:15:14,667
With Emma.

229
00:15:22,133 --> 00:15:24,200
That's my favorite song.

230
00:15:27,200 --> 00:15:28,900
No way.

231
00:15:29,033 --> 00:15:31,900
<i>That's the song Emma and I used
to dance to before.</i>

232
00:15:41,500 --> 00:15:43,733
<i> Emma, let's dance tonight.</i>

233
00:15:43,867 --> 00:15:45,200
<i> Sure.</i>

234
00:15:48,633 --> 00:15:51,533
<i>Your baby cologne smells really
good.</i>

235
00:15:51,667 --> 00:15:53,033
<i> I love its smell.</i>

236
00:15:53,167 --> 00:15:54,367
<i> Don't replace it.</i>

237
00:15:54,500 --> 00:15:55,867
<i> I really won't.</i>

238
00:15:56,000 --> 00:15:58,767
<i>So that you'll miss me
when I'm gone.</i>

239
00:15:58,900 --> 00:15:59,900
<i> What?</i>

240
00:16:00,033 --> 00:16:04,233
<i>Who said I want you to go away?</i>

241
00:16:04,367 --> 00:16:05,933
<i> Stop flattering me.</i>

242
00:16:06,067 --> 00:16:07,400
We didn't get married.

243
00:16:07,533 --> 00:16:11,267
But we dance to this song
on every occasion.

244
00:16:11,433 --> 00:16:14,133
We used to bring a cassette tape
back then.

245
00:16:17,733 --> 00:16:19,433
<i> That's our favorite.</i>

246
00:16:21,733 --> 00:16:24,433
You seem to be happy together
before.

247
00:16:24,567 --> 00:16:30,233
But you seem to have forgotten
her because you have Jade now.

248
00:16:32,000 --> 00:16:34,600
By how you put it,

249
00:16:34,733 --> 00:16:36,267
it sounded like I'm the only one
who did wrong.

250
00:16:39,133 --> 00:16:42,967
<i>I want us to dance to this song
on our wedding day.</i>

251
00:16:43,133 --> 00:16:44,300
<i> Of course.</i>

252
00:16:47,000 --> 00:16:52,033
Sorry, you reminded me of my ex.

253
00:16:52,167 --> 00:16:53,767
He cheated on me.

254
00:16:59,000 --> 00:17:00,900
How long has Emma been gone
for you

255
00:17:01,033 --> 00:17:02,467
to immediately replace her
with someone else?

256
00:17:03,700 --> 00:17:07,400
Are you sure she won't come back
anymore?

257
00:17:07,533 --> 00:17:12,267
What if she returns and you're
already with Jade?

258
00:17:14,400 --> 00:17:18,000
The problem with you is that you
play the victim.

259
00:17:19,200 --> 00:17:21,633
Why do you seem to be mad at me?

260
00:17:21,767 --> 00:17:23,467
You act as if you're Emma.

261
00:17:23,600 --> 00:17:25,100
Sorry.

262
00:17:25,233 --> 00:17:29,200
I'm just putting myself
in Emma's shoes.

263
00:17:29,333 --> 00:17:32,067
I feel bad for her.

264
00:17:32,200 --> 00:17:34,600
She's the real victim here.

265
00:17:34,733 --> 00:17:38,533
And Jade is the villainess.

266
00:17:38,667 --> 00:17:39,833
That's enough.

267
00:17:39,967 --> 00:17:43,367
Let's not talk about her anymore
because I want to forget her.

268
00:17:45,100 --> 00:17:47,200
<i> Is that so, Danilo?</i>

269
00:17:47,333 --> 00:17:49,267
<i> I won't let that happen.</i>

270
00:17:49,433 --> 00:17:51,900
<i> I will remind you of Emma.</i>

271
00:17:52,033 --> 00:17:54,367
<i>The woman you and Jade
cheated on.</i>

272
00:18:05,000 --> 00:18:06,367
<i>Let's show them
what we're made of.</i>

273
00:18:06,500 --> 00:18:07,400
<i> Okay.</i>

274
00:18:07,533 --> 00:18:09,567
Let's show them
what we're made of.

275
00:18:09,700 --> 00:18:12,400
Wait. Emma used to say the same
thing.

276
00:19:31,833 --> 00:19:33,933
That's how Emma and I
used to dance.

277
00:19:34,067 --> 00:19:36,033
How did you know that?

278
00:19:36,167 --> 00:19:37,733
Who really are you?

279
00:19:48,167 --> 00:19:49,133
I'll go get her.

280
00:19:49,267 --> 00:19:51,600
Boss, let Emma be.

281
00:19:51,733 --> 00:19:53,967
Looks like Danilo doesn't
recognize her.

282
00:19:55,233 --> 00:19:57,367
Does she really have to do that?

283
00:19:57,500 --> 00:19:59,567
She's getting carried away
by her emotions.

284
00:20:04,333 --> 00:20:05,967
Where's Danilo?

285
00:20:06,100 --> 00:20:08,133
Do you see him?

286
00:20:08,267 --> 00:20:10,467
Oh my! Look.

287
00:20:12,267 --> 00:20:13,767
What?

288
00:20:13,900 --> 00:20:16,200
I was gone for just a moment,

289
00:20:16,333 --> 00:20:19,267
and someone wanted
to steal my fiancé.

290
00:20:28,533 --> 00:20:29,867
Jade!

291
00:20:33,100 --> 00:20:35,500
How are you?

292
00:20:35,667 --> 00:20:37,467
How dare you touch me!

293
00:20:37,600 --> 00:20:39,267
Who are you? I don't know you!

294
00:20:39,400 --> 00:20:43,200
You're probably just pretending
not to know Logan Alvarez.

295
00:20:43,333 --> 00:20:45,367
You again?

296
00:20:45,500 --> 00:20:46,900
Why are you here?

297
00:20:47,033 --> 00:20:49,133
Why not?

298
00:20:49,267 --> 00:20:50,633
I'm one of the elite.

299
00:20:50,767 --> 00:20:53,767
Of course, Mrs. Ramirez
invited me.

300
00:20:53,900 --> 00:20:57,600
Hey, congratulations on your
successful launch of Activora.

301
00:20:57,733 --> 00:20:59,300
Do you need investors?

302
00:20:59,433 --> 00:21:02,733
No, I don't.
Anyway, I need to go.

303
00:21:02,867 --> 00:21:04,767
- Son of a gun.
- What are you doing?

304
00:21:04,900 --> 00:21:06,167
What's wrong with you?

305
00:21:07,300 --> 00:21:08,533
You.

306
00:21:08,700 --> 00:21:11,200
I've forgiven what you did
to me in Japan.

307
00:21:11,333 --> 00:21:12,600
And now you're giving me
the attitude?

308
00:21:12,733 --> 00:21:13,933
Let's talk.

309
00:21:15,133 --> 00:21:17,267
I don't have time for this,
Logan.

310
00:21:17,400 --> 00:21:19,033
If you'll excuse me.

311
00:21:19,167 --> 00:21:22,533
Why not... we dance?

312
00:21:22,667 --> 00:21:26,333
Let's dance, just like
what we used to do in Japan.

313
00:21:26,467 --> 00:21:27,233
What?

314
00:21:27,367 --> 00:21:28,800
Dance with me.

315
00:21:28,933 --> 00:21:30,633
Wait. Hey. Let go of me.

316
00:21:30,767 --> 00:21:32,433
Excuse us.

317
00:21:33,933 --> 00:21:35,733
Masters of the dance floor,
coming through.

318
00:21:37,300 --> 00:21:39,000
Show me your dance.

319
00:21:39,133 --> 00:21:42,567
What dance? Let me go!

320
00:21:42,733 --> 00:21:44,167
It's okay.

321
00:21:44,300 --> 00:21:46,300
Let go of me!

322
00:21:46,433 --> 00:21:47,733
I don't want to dance with you.

323
00:21:47,867 --> 00:21:49,067
Just let me go!

324
00:21:49,200 --> 00:21:51,300
Stop playing hard-to-get.

325
00:21:51,433 --> 00:21:55,733
We used to dance wilder
in Japan.

326
00:21:55,867 --> 00:21:57,233
This is so easy.

327
00:21:57,367 --> 00:21:59,067
What are you talking about?

328
00:22:08,133 --> 00:22:09,167
<i> Lift me up.</i>

329
00:22:09,300 --> 00:22:10,333
<i> What?</i>

330
00:22:10,467 --> 00:22:13,867
<i>That isn't part
of our dance steps.</i>

331
00:22:14,000 --> 00:22:16,533
<i>We'll show that off later
at the dance.</i>

332
00:22:16,700 --> 00:22:17,600
<i> Okay.</i>

333
00:22:28,000 --> 00:22:30,000
<i> I love you so much, Emma.</i>

334
00:22:30,133 --> 00:22:32,067
<i> I love you so much, too, Dan.</i>

335
00:22:48,900 --> 00:22:50,500
What are you doing? Let me go!

336
00:22:50,633 --> 00:22:53,100
Another woman is flirting
with my fiancé.

337
00:22:53,233 --> 00:22:54,733
Are you jealous?

338
00:22:54,867 --> 00:22:56,900
What will you do?
Will you stop her?

339
00:22:57,033 --> 00:22:58,333
Will you attack the woman?

340
00:22:58,467 --> 00:22:59,600
Yes!

341
00:22:59,733 --> 00:23:03,400
Because I won't let anyone
steal my fiancé!

342
00:23:03,533 --> 00:23:08,867
FYI, a thief hates a fellow
thief.

343
00:23:09,000 --> 00:23:12,433
I heard your fiancé
is already married.

344
00:23:12,567 --> 00:23:14,000
Is that right?

345
00:23:14,133 --> 00:23:15,700
That's not true.

346
00:23:15,833 --> 00:23:17,400
I'm the one who's always
left behind.

347
00:23:17,533 --> 00:23:19,433
I'm always the one being robbed.

348
00:23:24,100 --> 00:23:27,033
Wait. Excuse us.

349
00:23:27,167 --> 00:23:27,967
Sorry.

350
00:23:28,100 --> 00:23:30,567
I'm still dancing.

351
00:23:33,833 --> 00:23:35,733
<i> Watch me, Jade.</i>

352
00:23:41,733 --> 00:23:43,533
No!

353
00:23:45,800 --> 00:23:48,733
Since you can already walk
and seem okay now,

354
00:23:48,867 --> 00:23:51,000
you can go home, Zayn.

355
00:23:51,133 --> 00:23:52,133
Confess first.

356
00:23:55,033 --> 00:23:55,967
Fine.

357
00:23:57,167 --> 00:23:59,000
I like you.

358
00:23:59,133 --> 00:24:00,933
Happy?

359
00:24:01,067 --> 00:24:02,600
Boss, wait!

360
00:24:02,733 --> 00:24:04,167
Can you calm down?

361
00:24:04,300 --> 00:24:05,633
I can't!

362
00:24:05,767 --> 00:24:07,667
What if Jade catches Emma?

363
00:24:07,800 --> 00:24:09,433
All our plans will get ruined.

364
00:24:09,567 --> 00:24:11,500
I know it's you, Emma.

365
00:24:11,633 --> 00:24:14,000
Won't you return for Mookie?

366
00:24:16,100 --> 00:24:17,700
Even just for your daughter?

367
00:24:20,433 --> 00:24:22,067
Emma, I need to know.

368
00:24:22,200 --> 00:24:24,433
Tell me the truth.

369
00:24:24,567 --> 00:24:26,533
Do you still love Danilo?
